commit 08844c84c0d9d6409942a0a6948fc4354b842ac3
Author: Trevor <trevor@confident-ai.com>
Date:   Thu Dec 4 12:39:38 2025 -0700

    refactor(models): unify model API and normalize SDK kwargs
    
    - integrate unified model refactor with consistent argument validation
    - standardize model ctors to accept (name/model, api_key, temperature,
      generation_kwargs, **kwargs) across providers
    - use normalize_kwargs_and_extract_aliases in all models to:
      - remap deprecated aliases (e.g. model, _openai_api_key,
        _anthropic_api_key, azure_endpoint, etc.)
      - keep only sanitized extras in self.kwargs for downstream SDK config
    - pass **self.kwargs into super().__init__(...) so DeepEvalBaseLLM can
      forward user kwargs through load_model(...) to the underlying SDK
    - ensure API keys are stored as SecretStr on Settings / models but passed
      to SDK clients as plain strings (OpenAI, Azure, Gemini, Ollama, Grok,
      etc.)
    - fix OpenAIEmbeddingModel to pass model name into the base class so
      the embedding client always receives a valid model parameter
    - fix check_if_multimodal to return False when no multimodal sentinel is
      present, avoiding accidental multimodal wrapping of plain text prompts
    - update tests to:
      - verify ctor keys override Settings and that legacy alias keywords are
        not forwarded in client kwargs
      - patch SDK clients (OpenAI, AzureOpenAI, xai_sdk.Client, etc.) instead
        of importing them directly in core tests

commit af1f8ccb97327a7f30029eef5acc81c57712362c
Author: Trevor <trevor@confident-ai.com>
Date:   Thu Dec 4 07:45:55 2025 -0700

    fix(utils): only treat prompts with image tags as multimodal
    
    Previously check_if_multimodal() always returned True because
    it tested `matches is not None` after calling re.finditer(),
    which always returns a list.
    
    This caused plain-text prompts to be wrapped in multimodal
    content arrays, breaking AzureOpenAIModel.generate() tests.
    Now we return bool(matches) so "no match" cases are treated
    as non-multimodal.

    explicitly flush and fsync before releasing portalocker locks, preventing
    truncated or partially written files in parallel runs on network storage.

    - Harden TestRunManager.save_test_run and save_final_test_run_link JSON writes
    - Harden Prompt._write_to_cache JSON writes for the prompt cache
    - Add tests asserting flush & fsync behavior for test runs and prompt cache
    
    Fixes #2322.

commit 0e41142f092f0e448080fb7bf54b51f096b7edc5
Author: BloggerBust <trevor.wilson@bloggerbust.ca>
Date:   Wed Oct 29 23:15:06 2025 -0600

    fix(test_run): preserve in-memory TestRun on disk I/O failures
    
    Avoid nulling `self.test_run` on I/O errors. Only overwrite on
    successful load and warn otherwise. In `update_test_run`, fall back to
    in-memory update. Ensure parent dir exists before saving. Maybe that
    will help avoid some I/O errors.
    
    Add unit tests covering:
    
    - read lock contention
    - missing file
    - malformed JSON
    - update fallback on read failure
    
    Fixes #2243

commit 6abfc43fc914498034fbe0d66c1b0ca85ce786f4

Author: BloggerBust <trevor.wilson@bloggerbust.ca>

    test(core): preserve *_API_KEY secrets in env sandbox
    
    Derive `PRESERVE_FROM_BASELINE` from `Settings.model_fields` (suffix
    `_API_KEY`, excluding `CONFIDENT*`) and re-inject only these after
    clearing all Settings env vars via `monkeypatch`. This protects CI
    secrets from being clobbered. Also removes the empty `test_config/conftest.py`.
    
    We exclude CONFIDENT* because confidet api keys are not meant for test_core

commit cfde82cad0cf49ab06174a602ce211893107e1ce
Author: BloggerBust <trevor.wilson@bloggerbust.ca>
Date:   Mon Oct 27 23:12:29 2025 -0600

    feat(evaluate,settings,retry): cooperative timeouts and persist on cancel
    
    - Add outer-deadline budgeting using ContextVar and `resolve_effective_attempt_timeout`
    - Enforce task caps via `_await_with_outer_deadline` and `run_sync_with_timeout`
    - Always persist test cases and metrics on cancel or timeout
    - New settings: `DEEPEVAL_PER_ATTEMPT_TIMEOUT_SECONDS_OVERRIDE`, `DEEPEVAL_PER_TASK_TIMEOUT_SECONDS_OVERRIDE`, `DEEPEVAL_TASK_GATHER_BUFFER_SECONDS_OVERRIDE`, `DEEPEVAL_LOG_STACK_TRACES`
    - Mark `CancelledError` as timeout in metric paths
    - improve gather timeout handling
    - Default OpenAI client `timeout` from settings
    - Add extensive tests for LLM/MLLM/Conversational/Agentic paths
    - Minor fixes: indicator async_mode check, progress updates, verbose logging
    
    BREAKING CHANGE: use `*_OVERRIDE` settings (`DEEPEVAL_PER_ATTEMPT_TIMEOUT_SECONDS_OVERRIDE`, `DEEPEVAL_PER_TASK_TIMEOUT_SECONDS_OVERRIDE`, `DEEPEVAL_TASK_GATHER_BUFFER_SECONDS_OVERRIDE`) instead of setting the computed fields directly

commit 59e147ebf35754199c8bc0387d2ccadee8c59dae
Author: Trevor <trevor@confident-ai.com>
Date:   Tue Oct 21 10:41:27 2025 -0600

    feat(execute): remove return_exceptions in try path and make DFS children tasks for proper cancel
    
    - remove return_exceptions=True from `asyncio.gather(*tasks)` in
    try path, but on `TimeoutError` drain with `return_exceptions=True`, then re-raise.
    - Schedule DFS child spans via `asyncio.create_task` for correct cancellation.
    - Add `_SleepyMetric` test stub and refactor per-task-timeout test to use it.
    - Keeps upstream error propagation semantics and improves reliability under timeouts.

commit 2ed0c90742ff6171f5132010f9b0c9a2d78e398a
Author: BloggerBust <trevor.wilson@bloggerbust.ca>
Date:   Fri Oct 17 13:50:00 2025 -0600

    fix(execute): return early from dfs on errored spans and enforce LLMTestCase for span metrics in loop runner
    
    - async dfs: after evaluating a span, skip traversing children when `_skip_metrics_for_error` is true.
    - Looped sync dfs: return early when no metrics, but when metrics exist without an `LLMTestCase` and no TaskCompletion, mark span `ERRORED`, set formatted error, and advance the progress bar.

commit c8514c3779e8200d3889cc6eab68ae6dcd220cc5

    - Replace `str(e)` with `format_error_text(...)` for span/trace errors and `metric.error`.
    - Use `format_error_text` in `on_task_done` for both exceptions and cancellations. Reuse captured `exc` to avoid re-calling `t.exception()`

commit 20d5a76b4b92db39fe2f0c3bcf8f682e708731d4
Author: BloggerBust <trevor.wilson@bloggerbust.ca>
Date:   Thu Oct 16 12:03:43 2025 -0600

commit c33d832cc6b328f0fa8c996c9626fe9a1e535200
Author: BloggerBust <trevor.wilson@bloggerbust.ca>
Date:   Thu Oct 16 11:17:39 2025 -0600

    fix(execute): stop early returns in golden loop
    
    Introduce `skip_metrics_for_this_golden` to avoid aborting evaluation for a
    golden when LLMTestCase is missing or lacks `actual_output`.
    Instead, mark the trace or span ERRORED, advance progress bars, and
    continue. This prevents partial runs from silently terminating the
    loop and ensures span-level metrics and trace results are still captured where possible.
    
    - Add `skip_metrics_for_this_golden` in both `execute_agentic_test_cases`
      and `execute_agentic_test_cases_from_loop`.
    - Replace early `return`s with flag-setting; only run trace-level metrics
      when not skipping, but still perform span DFS.
    - Guard metric execution loops accordingly and keep progress updates intact.
    - In looped execution, add missing
      `test_results.extend(extract_trace_test_results(trace_api))`
      to align with the non-loop path.

commit a625171e83f52b56696f1a5fded9f56a4d3e9edc
Author: BloggerBust <trevor.wilson@bloggerbust.ca>
Date:   Wed Oct 15 21:10:26 2025 -0600

    feat(errors,evaluate,tracing): friendlier error surfacing
    
    - Introduce error taxonomy: `DeepEvalError`, `UserAppError`
    - make `MissingTestCaseParamsError` and `MismatchedTestCaseInputsError` subclasses and clarify docstrings.
    - Add non-fatal guards across both sync and async trace & span paths: when LLMTestCase is missing or `actual_output` is `None`, mark ERRORED and attach compact, typed messages; continue evaluation.
    - Implement `_skip_metrics_for_error` and `_trace_error`
    - propagate status and error to root span and API spans; avoid measuring metrics under failed nodes.
    - Surface async task exceptions and cancels in
    - `a_execute_agentic_test_cases_from_loop` via `on_task_done` by marking the associated trace or root span ERRORED.
    - Improve progress accuracy with `count_total_metrics_for_trace` and
     `count_metrics_in_span_subtree`, use those calcs to fast-forward bars on skips.

commit 9b8efc96e2dca4e9c83a2cc3d7343de397438e2e
Author: BloggerBust <trevor.wilson@bloggerbust.ca>
Date:   Wed Oct 8 23:06:51 2025 -0600

    fix(core-tests): sandbox env per test to prevent settings leaks
    
    Introduce autouse `_env_sandbox` that snapshots/restores `os.environ` and calls `reset_settings()` before and after each test. This prevents mutations from `settings.edit(persist=False)` (which updates process env) from leaking across tests and affecting timeouts/retry policy, etc.

commit c046de3337943adcb13556eab279d19147e37d13
Author: Mayank Solanki <bizmiku@gmail.com>
Date:   Wed Oct 8 20:57:44 2025 +0530

commit f95d752dde2edfac51e0e16b16a51f119069752e
Author: BloggerBust <trevor.wilson@bloggerbust.ca>
Date:   Wed Oct 8 09:23:38 2025 -0600

    test(core): remove invalid env fallback test for retry settings
    
    The `dynamic_stop_invalid_env_falls_back` case is no longer valid.
    `DEEPEVAL_RETRY_MAX_ATTEMPTS` is now sourced via Pydantic settings with
    strong typing and validation, so a non-integer value
    fails validation at config load rather than flowing through to
    `dynamic_stop`. The previous "fall back to default attempts" behavior
    cannot occur under the new settings model.

commit c5f78b129808cf030d9e37a516b7bcd093b32766
Author: BloggerBust <trevor.wilson@bloggerbust.ca>
Date:   Tue Sep 30 15:48:25 2025 -0600

    fix(tests): avoid IsADirectoryError in CI when scanning tmp_path for output
    
    The autouse fixture creates a .deepeval/ directory in each tests tmp_path.
    The printing test iterated tmp_path.iterdir() and called read_text on
    every entry, which in CI was hitting the .deepeval/ directory first
    and raised IsADirectoryError. This commit addresses that issue.

commit 62ef0f800a00c7ea98ed5210e11a8d0c68f16101
Author: himanushi <himanushi@users.noreply.github.com>
Date:   Thu Oct 2 17:48:49 2025 +0900

    fix: Remove gpt-5-chat-latest from models_requiring_temperature_1
    
    gpt-5-chat-latest is NOT a reasoning model, unlike gpt-5/o1/o3 series.
    It is a standard chat model that supports flexible temperature values.
    
    Evidence:
    1. API testing confirms temperature=0.0 works without errors
    2. Response shows reasoning_tokens=0 (reasoning models have reasoning_tokens>0)
    3. gpt-5 (reasoning model) explicitly rejects temperature!=1.0
    
    Tested with OpenAI API:
    - gpt-5 + temperature=0.0  Error: only supports default (1)
    - gpt-5-chat-latest + temperature=0.0  Success
    - gpt-5-chat-latest response: reasoning_tokens=0 (not a reasoning model)

    docs(cli): add CLI guide with patterns, persistence, and retry notes
    
    Introduce the `docs/docs/cli.mdx` page that documents the CLI by patterns (set/unset pairs, provider switching) rather than per-command, to reduce churn ahead of a future UX consistency pass.

    * Document `set-debug`/`unset-debug` flags at a high level
    * Clarify provider switching semantics, enables one provider and disables others.
    * Outline available provider pairs with typical flags; defer exact options to `--help`.
    * Add retry policy section, including opt-out list via `DEEPEVAL_SDK_RETRY_PROVIDERS`, log-level validators, and backoff settings.

    - Resolve `expected_output` from the active Golden only if its `input`
    matches the candidate (case/space-insensitive).
    - stash `_function_kwargs` on span during observer __enter__
    - Infer candidate input from `test_case.input` -> span.input ->
    observer call args -> trace.input
    - Add tests covering input match/mismatch, observer arg fallback, and direct `input=` kwargs

commit b24c56de3bbe7be1eae22e604a8f53dc51cb8d71
Author: BloggerBust <trevor.wilson@bloggerbust.ca>
Date:   Thu Sep 25 10:45:34 2025 -0600

    fix(tracing): gate `expected_output` resolution on Golden input match
    
    This prevents unexpected `expected_output` resolution when nested tools/agents use different inputs, aligning behavior with issue #1983s expectations.
    
    - Update `_resolve_expected_output_from_context` to accept
    `candidate_input` and only inherit `expected_output` from the active
    Golden when `golden.input` matches the candidate input using
    case/whitespace-insensitive normalization.
    - apply the new check through `update_current_trace` and
    `update_current_span` so spans/traces do not inherit surprising values
    due to input mismatch.
    - Add integration tests in `tests/test_core/test_tracing/test_execute_integration.py`:

commit c7cbb548a6d389144d188a606a339f6a4eeaec06
Author: BloggerBust <trevor.wilson@bloggerbust.ca>
Date:   Wed Sep 24 15:45:31 2025 -0600

    feat(evaluate,tracing): resolve component level expected_output from dataset context
    
    This PR lets component level evals pick up `expected_output` from the dataset
    automatically, removing the need for hard-coded "..." in tools.
    
    Introduce a dataset scoped ContextVar (CURRENT_GOLDEN) and wrap per golden
    execution (both sync + async) so user code runs with the active Golden bound to
    context. Update tracing to resolve missing expected_output from the active
    Golden
    
    - add deepeval/dataset/context.py with CURRENT_GOLDEN and helpers
    - wrap execute_agentic_test_cases_from_loop / a_execute_agentic_test_cases_from_loop
      to set/reset CURRENT_GOLDEN around `yield golden`
    - tracing: implement _resolve_expected_output_from_context and use it from
      update_current_span / update_current_trace (both test_case and fallback paths)
    - utils: add is_missing to check for None or whitespace
    
    Closes #1983.

commit 8397e9cd6b4a2134fc3e98b8d367b0758f2457ce
Author: BloggerBust <trevor.wilson@bloggerbust.ca>
Date:   Fri Sep 19 16:59:38 2025 -0600

    refactor(async): remove unused global evaluation task cache
    
    We now track and gather tasks per loop. The global cache is no longer
    read and is not needed. The cache posed cross loop task management
    risks, which is why we have moved away from it.
    
    - Delete `global_evaluation_tasks` singleton and related imports.
    - Stop appending to the global cache in `EvaluationDataset.evaluate()`;
      still coerce the task to ensure validation/side effects run.
    - Remove finalizers that cleared the global cache in
      `execute.py` looped paths.

commit 90acbbe4a9a4a037eacb5b0d85c4d931471e817d
Author: BloggerBust <trevor.wilson@bloggerbust.ca>
Date:   Fri Sep 19 13:32:28 2025 -0600

    test(CI): put back finally cleanup block

commit f408e69ec992a550b22675daefac02f2efd31eb2
Author: BloggerBust <trevor.wilson@bloggerbust.ca>
Date:   Fri Sep 19 13:14:36 2025 -0600

    test: temporarily commented code to verify CI test behavior

commit 397da91ba164401c601ea0ae2f2a01c3e714f266
Author: BloggerBust <trevor.wilson@bloggerbust.ca>
Date:   Fri Sep 19 12:11:50 2025 -0600

    fix(async): snapshot loop tasks and cancel strays in agentic iterator
    
    Add _snapshot_tasks() and use it to:
    - Take a baseline snapshot of tasks on the current loop before yielding goldens.
    - After gather, detect leftover tasks not in the baseline or created_tasks,
      then log, cancel, and drain them (when DEEPEVAL_DEBUG_ASYNC is enabled).
    
    Also remove the redundant `asyncio.create_task = loop.create_task` assignment
    before trace evaluation as we already restore the original create_task earlier.
    
    This reduces hangs caused by tasks leaking across iterations/loops and ensures
    only tasks created in the current run are awaited.

commit c817f1dc44c3fb22b54247969968bf241a7bd50b
Author: BloggerBust <trevor.wilson@bloggerbust.ca>
Date:   Fri Sep 19 12:26:59 2025 -0600

    feat: Add task timeout handling and logging for stalled tasks
    
    - Implemented logging to track per task and gather timeouts separately.
    - Added task metadata collection to help debug stalled tasks.
    - Enhanced logging with suggestions for increasing timeout values.
    - Introduced `DEEPEVAL_PER_TASK_TIMEOUT_SECONDS` and `DEEPEVAL_TASK_GATHER_BUFFER_SECONDS` for configuration of task and gather timeouts.

commit 8a9797123f73fc174f0be34d7e5aa0bb4b1ad735
Author: BloggerBust <trevor.wilson@bloggerbust.ca>
Date:   Fri Sep 19 12:26:04 2025 -0600

    fix(async,ci): prevent coroutine re-await & stabilize async evals
    
    - Track and gather only tasks created on the current loop during evals to avoid
      cannot reuse already awaited coroutine and cross loop errors.
    - Introduce coerce_to_task() to normalize Task/Future/coroutine/awaitable inputs.
    - Refactor EvaluationTasks to store asyncio Futures, return copies from get_tasks(),
      and provide a clear_tasks() that cancels pending tasks before clearing.
    - call loop.shutdown_asyncgens() in tracing worker before close.
    - Replace blocking time.sleep() with await asyncio.sleep() in async test helper.
    - CI: add maintainer only full test workflow with secrets gating & concurrency
    - Ruff cleanups

commit b38b1bdc809fed98f2439a0f43520497ad38593b
Author: BloggerBust <trevor.wilson@bloggerbust.ca>
Date:   Thu Sep 11 12:09:53 2025 -0600

    docs(getting-started, flags-and-configs): document retry/backoff defaults and env flags
    
    - Add Retries & backoff (default behavior) to Getting Started:
      - Retries once on transient errors (network/timeouts, 5xx)
      - 429s retried unless marked non-retryable (OpenAI: `insufficient_quota`)
      - Exponential backoff with jitter (initial 1s, base 2, jitter 2s, cap 5s)
      - Link to Environment Flags section
    
    - Add Environment Flags table to Flags and Configs with:
      - DEEPEVAL_RETRY_MAX_ATTEMPTS
      - DEEPEVAL_RETRY_INITIAL_SECONDS
      - DEEPEVAL_RETRY_EXP_BASE
      - DEEPEVAL_RETRY_JITTER
      - DEEPEVAL_RETRY_CAP_SECONDS
      - Note about ignoring non-finite/below-minimum values

commit 1b39325445bfd871bef621cf15b555b138aa688e

Date:   Thu Sep 11 11:49:55 2025 -0600

    fix(utils): guard `read_env_float` against NaN/Inf; add unit tests
    
    * fix(utils): treat non-finite floats as invalid in `read_env_float` (fallback to defaults).
    * test(retry\_policy): add comprehensive offline tests for `extract_error_code` and `make_is_transient`
    * test(utils): add tests for `read_env_int`/`read_env_float` (valid/invalid/min cases) and env-driven overrides for `default_wait`/`default_stop`, including fallback on invalid env values.
    
    This prevents `default_wait()` from inheriting a NaN `exp_base` and improves coverage of retry policy behavior.

commit beee98ce5ccb3d20717f59fb2ced7cf16e63473c
Author: BloggerBust <trevor.wilson@bloggerbust.ca>
Date:   Sat Aug 16 16:16:13 2025 -0600

    feat(models): add SDK-agnostic retry policy and wire OpenAI LLM to it
    
    * Introduce `deepeval/models/retry_policy.py` with:
    
      * `ErrorPolicy` for classifying transient vs non-retryable errors
      * `extract_error_code` (response/body/message markers)
      * `make_is_transient` + `retry_predicate`
      * Env-tunable defaults: `default_wait` / `default_stop`
      * OpenAI preset (`OPENAI_ERROR_POLICY`) and `OPENAI_MESSAGE_MARKERS`
      * `__all__` for explicit exports
    
    * Update `deepeval/models/llms/openai_model.py` to use the new policy:
    
      * Replace ad-hoc Tenacity config with `_base_retry_rules_kw`
      * Add `before_sleep_log` + structured error logging
      * Disable OpenAI SDK internal retries via `_openai_client_kwargs()` (`max_retries=0`)
      * Route `load_model()` through shared kwargs
      * Remove legacy `retryable_exceptions`
    
    * Add helpers to `deepeval/utils.py`:
    
      * `read_env_int` and `read_env_float` with docstrings & min-value guards
    
    New env overrides (with sane defaults):
    
    * `DEEPEVAL_RETRY_MAX_ATTEMPTS`
    * `DEEPEVAL_RETRY_INITIAL_SECONDS`
    * `DEEPEVAL_RETRY_EXP_BASE`
    * `DEEPEVAL_RETRY_JITTER`
    * `DEEPEVAL_RETRY_CAP_SECONDS`
    
    This unifies retry semantics across providers, treats quota-exhausted 429s as
    non-retryable, retries network timeouts and 5xx, and avoids double-retrying at
    the SDK layer.

Date:   Thu Sep 11 11:30:27 2025 -0600

    fix(tracing): strip NUL bytes from JSON to prevent Postgres 22P05
    
    Postgres rejects U+0000 in text/jsonb, causing 22P05 during /v1/test-run.
    We now remove real NUL bytes from all strings inside make_json_serializable,
    so dumped/posted trace bodies are safe.

commit b1dec13531f752e96c82e2368fa194063d4341f5
Author: BloggerBust <trevor.wilson@bloggerbust.ca>
Date:   Mon Sep 8 17:15:56 2025 -0600

    feat(config,utils)!: introduce Pydantic-based Settings and unified dotenv autoload
    
    - Move dotenv autoloading into deepeval/config/settings.py with clear precedence:
      .env -> .env.{APP_ENV} -> .env.local; process env always wins; opt out via DEEPEVAL_DISABLE_DOTENV; support ENV_DIR_PATH (expands ~ and $VARS).
    - Add Settings (pydantic-settings) to centralize env variables; all optional by design.
      * Validators:
        - Booleans coerced via parse_bool (accepts 1/0, yes/no, on/off, enabled/disabled).
        - Paths (DEEPEVAL_RESULTS_FOLDER, ENV_DIR_PATH) expand ~ and $VARS.
        - Floats accept "", "none", "null" -> None (cost overrides, TEMPERATURE).
        - TEMPERATURE constrained with confloat(ge=0, le=2).
        - URL-like fields typed as AnyUrl.
        - DEEPEVAL_DEFAULT_SAVE validated as "dotenv" or "dotenv:<path>" with path expansion.
        - DEEPEVAL_FILE_SYSTEM normalized (READ_ONLY, RO -> READ_ONLY).
    - Refactor utils:
      * Add parse_bool, get_env_bool, bool_to_env_str, set_env_bool.
      * Replace YES/NO checks with canonical helpers; reading remains backward compatible.
    - Wire __init__.py to call autoload_dotenv() from config.settings.
    - Remove legacy deepeval/env.py.
    - Add dependencies: pydantic and pydantic-settings to pyproject.toml.
    
    BREAKING CHANGE: env booleans written by helpers are now serialized as
    "1"/"0" instead of "YES"/"NO". Reading still accepts previous values,
    but if any external
    tooling relied on our old output format, that tooling will need to be updated.

commit ff934539e3bb777148633e79a3b5bc80b3cda277
Author: BloggerBust <trevor.wilson@bloggerbust.ca>
Date:   Sun Sep 7 15:25:44 2025 -0600

    feat(synthesizer): add markdown loaders and improve lazy imports
    
    * Refactor `DocumentChunker` to use lazy getters (`_get_langchain`, `_get_chromadb`)
      instead of module-level imports and global flags.
    * Add markdown family support in loaders: `.md`, `.markdown`, `.mdx`.
    * Switch type hints to quoted forward refs and gate heavy types behind `TYPE_CHECKING`.
    * Use `TokenTextSplitter` via lazy import; remove direct annotations on instances.
    * Store Chroma metadata as plain dicts
    * Defer loader mapping initialization until first use.
    
    docs:
    
    * Update `synthesizer-generate-from-docs.mdx` to list required deps
      (`chromadb`, `langchain-core`, `langchain-community`, `langchain-text-splitters`),
      clarify token-based chunking, and add markdown formats to examples.
    * Update `synthesizer-introduction.mdx` and `guides-using-synthesizer.mdx`
      to include markdown formats and fix minor copy/grammar.
    * Add explicit note in `integrations/vector-databases/chroma.mdx` that
      `generate_goldens_from_docs()` **requires** Chroma.
    
    test:
    
    * Add comprehensive `test_doc_chunker.py` covering:
    
      * markdown loader behavior and encoding autodetect,
      * lazy import error paths (LangChain/Chroma),
      * chunking preconditions, batching, metadata,
      * async chunking path,
      * collection cache hits and persistent path/collection naming.
    * Add `tests/test_core/conftest.py` shim to substitute `pysqlite3` for `sqlite3`
      in CI environments with older SQLite.
    
    build:
    
    * Add `pysqlite3-binary` to `pyproject.toml` and lockfile to satisfy Chromas
      sqlite >= 3.35 requirement in constrained environments.

    - Clarified that dotenv loading is optional, with precedence and opt-out env var
    
    This removes unnecessary distraction from the Quick Start Flow.

    refactor(init): load dotenv before all other import

    feat(env): autoload .env/.env.local at import time; add example & docs
    
    - Add `deepeval/env.py` and call `autoload_dotenv()` from `deepeval/__init__.py`
      so `.env.local` then `.env` are loaded automatically at import.

    - Ignore `.env.local` in git.
    - Update README and docs:

      - Evaluation Flags: environment variables table and note on autoload behavior.
      - OpenAI integration: prefer `.env.local`, keep shell/CI and notebook alternatives.
      - Ollama integration: environment setup with `OLLAMA_HOST`.
    - Add `python-dotenv` dependency.

commit c1a7e9ef634cb5241f2476bd0ca0752dbc7d23a2
Author: Trevor <trevor@inflection.ai>
Date:   Mon Aug 25 14:08:51 2025 -0700

    Change benchmarks to use pydantic classes for evaluate results
    
    Adds strongly typed pydantic interfaces as the return values for all benchmarks to resolve #1948
    
    Currently the `evaluate` function is annotated as `... -> Dict`, but in reality most of the benchmarks return a float. In the case of the `IFEval` it returns a dict, so this PR uses inheritance with pydantic models to support returning the base `overall_accuracy` based interface to the client. However, if they choose to specialize their response into `IFEvalResult` then they have the ability to access the `IFEval` specific fields.
    
    I have manually tested both `IFEval` and random other benchmarks and verified that the code functions properly
    
    An example block that can use this inheritance is something like
    
    ```
        def evaluate(
            self, model: BaseRESTModel, logger: BenchmarkLogger | None = None, **kwargs
        ) -> BenchmarkResult | None:
            results: DeepEvalBaseBenchmarkResult = self.benchmark.evaluate(model, **kwargs)
            bm_result = BenchmarkResult(
                overall_score=results.overall_accuracy, individual_scores={}, name=self.get_name()
            )
            return bm_result
    ```
    where `BenchmarkResult` is another pydantic model. Essentially, these changes ensures that the result of each benchmark follows a specified format and also supports serializing to dict/json if the user needs that (hence why a Pydantic model is chosen over a raw dataclass).
    
    
    It is worth noting that **this is a breaking change**, if that is undesirable then I can convert this PR to have new functions called `evaluate_typed` or something similar. Though in my opinion, it is better for the project long term to enforce every benchmark to only use typed models and warn users in release notes of this change (this could be something done later down the line).
    
    This PR also pins datasets to `<4.0.0` as many benchmarks are reliant on data loader scripts which were deprecated in 4.0.0 causing issues.

commit 49b9b248745bf3255739198bc52e2bb208a3d9e5
Author: Trevor <trevor@inflection.ai>
Date:   Wed Aug 20 15:06:56 2025 -0700

    Improve polymorphism of DeepEvalBaseBenchmark
    
    Currently, every instance of `DeepEvalBaseLLM` is expected to have an `evaluate` api that takes in a required `model` argument and then uses that model to output a dict.
    
    This PR just codifies the interfaces and adds `kwargs` so that a script can call any benchmark with arbitrary kwargs (that may not apply to this benchmark, such as `batch_size`).
    
    The main use case of this is suppose we have a list of benchmarks
    
    ```
    benchmarks: list[DeepEvalBaseBenchmark] = [TruthfulQA(), SQuAD()]
    kwargs = {"batch_size": 3}
    chosen_benchmark_idx: int = ...
    model = ...
    
    benchmarks[chosen_benchmark_idx].evaluate(model, **kwargs)
    ```
    
    This will allow us to run `SQuAD`, which does **NOT** have a `batch_size` argument without crashing, and if we choose to run `TruthfulQA`, then the `batch_size` will be parsed in the function.
    
    However, if you were to attempt this with the current code you will encounter the error
    ```
    SQuAD.evaluate() got an unexpected keyword argument 'batch_size'
    ```

commit 23c59546f0139d63abd40d03eb49f77fae3d10ee
Author: Connor Brinton <connor@brintonium.com>
Date:   Wed Aug 20 15:22:11 2025 -0400

     Import `ConversationalGEval` in code example
    
    The "Multi-Turn" tab on the "Getting Started" includes a code example. Currently this code example does not work properly because it uses `ConversationalGEval`, which is never imported. These changes replace the unused `GEval` import with `ConversationalGEval`, which is presumably what was intended originally. This fixes the code example so that it works properly.

commit 1d0a6861dd7a1601f238345be1e106796e3e9b00
Author: BloggerBust <trevor.wilson@bloggerbust.ca>
Date:   Fri Aug 15 19:16:43 2025 -0600

    fix(openai_model): add missing commas in model lists to prevent silent string concatenation
    
    Python concatenates adjacent string literals; without commas the lists
    `structured_outputs_models` and `models_requiring_temperature_1`
    accidentally merged two entries into one. This can cause model-name
    capability checks to behave incorrectly.
    
    No behavioral changes beyond the fix. Ran black on the file.

commit 00d8e768bc2721148437520965c4cb4d709a24fb
Author: Aaron McClintock <41651816+Spectavi@users.noreply.github.com>
Date:   Thu May 29 17:59:28 2025 -0700

    Improve AnswerRelevancy template
    
    Discourages breaking single words into a statement if it's part of a larger, coherent statement. Smaller models will sometimes split the document into so many "statements" that it over-runs the context window leading to malformed, incomplete JSON outputs.

commit 874bab425a6a461737d5822b78a00734ba97b8dc
Author: Serghei Iakovlev <git@serghei.pl>
Date:   Mon May 5 19:36:17 2025 +0200

    Introduce get_actual_model_name() model helper
    
    This function is useful for extracting the actual model name from a
    provider-prefixed format which is used by some proxies like LiteLLM.
    LiteLLM is designed to work with many different LLM providers (OpenAI, Anthropic,
    Cohere, etc.). To tell it which provider's API to call, you prepend the provider
    name to the model ID, in the form "<provider>/<model>". So openai/gpt-4.1-mini
    literally means "OpenAI's GPT-4.1 Mini via the OpenAI chat completions endpoint."

commit 5b8d7c48b41f1251fe8326e9a0594878e84a4c94
Merge: 85053903 996254c7
Author: krishna0125 <40312441+krishna0125@users.noreply.github.com>
Date:   Tue Apr 29 12:40:56 2025 +0530

    Merge pull request #1 from krishna0125/krishna0125-mmlu-output-format_fix
    
    update mmlu.py
    
    This PR fixes an issue where the model.generate() method returns a tuple or list of results instead of a single object. Previously, accessing res.answer directly caused a TypeError because res was a tuple containing the MultipleChoiceSchema object. The fix safely checks if the result is a tuple or list and extracts the first element before accessing .answer. This ensures compatibility with different return types from the models generate() method and prevents runtime errors.
    
    Let me know if you want it more detailed or more concise!

    Update mmlu.py
    
    This PR fixes an issue where the model.generate() method returns a tuple or list of results instead of a single object. Previously, accessing res.answer directly caused a TypeError because res was a tuple containing the MultipleChoiceSchema object. The fix safely checks if the result is a tuple or list and extracts the first element before accessing .answer. This ensures compatibility with different return types from the models generate() method and prevents runtime errors.
    
    Let me know if you want it more detailed or more concise!

commit b44678adca90a39243c37f63fa7aac3637a9f012
Author: Dmitriy Vasilyuk <111213624+reasonmethis@users.noreply.github.com>
Date:   Sat Feb 22 17:32:07 2025 -0800

    Relax grpcio version constraint "1.67.1" -> "^1.67.1"
    
    Changed grpcio dependency from an exact version (`1.67.1`) to a caret constraint (`^1.67.1`) in `pyproject.toml`. This prevents the errors such as the following, when using `pip install -U deepeval` in a project that already uses grpcio:
    
    ```
    ERROR: pip's dependency resolver does not currently take into account all the packages that are installed. This behaviour is the source of the following dependency conflicts.
    grpcio-status 1.68.1 requires grpcio>=1.68.1, but you have grpcio 1.67.1 which is incompatible.
    ```

commit 8a91d4efbf1c109f785917c2e6abf98072b19590
Author: Anindyadeep <anindya@pop-os.localdomain>
Date:   Thu Nov 23 09:25:12 2023 +0530

    Refactor: Introduced the model_map and it's corresponding function inside summac model.
    
    Since, the SummaC model is been inspired from the implementation of https://github.com/tingofurro/summac
    and that implemenattion only requires the specific strucutre of the model_map. So, keeping those function
    and dict just there.

commit af2e20328ebb39aa5cb14e75fdf05e559dae213b
Author: Anindyadeep <anindya@pop-os.localdomain>
Date:   Thu Nov 23 09:22:46 2023 +0530

    Removed: model_map
    
    The reason of removing the model_map is the following:
    
    - The schema of the model map is very much focussed for the summac model and other
    keys of the schema is not been used by other models.
    
    - Since, we do not have a general schema for all of the models, so it is just introducing
    un-necessary complication in the structure. We can have a dedicated config where we can store
    different configurations later. But for now, we can remove to keep things simple.
